    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ring-shaped attachments to lamps, usually of brass, which surround the opening of the font, and are threaded inside to receive the screw of the burner.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000036051/Russell, Heritage of Light (1968)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ringvormige bevestigingen aan lampen, meestal van koper, die om de opening van het brandstofreservoir heen zitten en die aan de binnenkant een schroefdraad hebben om de schroef van de brander in te kunnen draaien.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>燈上的環形組件，通常以黃銅製成，環繞油壺開口四周，其內側刻有螺纹，可與燃燒器的螺栓相扣。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
